{
  "doc_id": "51112",
  "text": "Conceptualization of learning has been changing. Although the knowledge gain documented in this study represents strong evidence of learning, learner conceptual change is increasingly considered to be the ultimate indication that learning has been accomplished [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Evidence is clear that students demonstrated learning achievement in their responses to the standardized tests, but it is unclear whether the curriculum provided an experience deep enough to elicit a fundamental conceptual change in their knowledge base about fitness, benefits from physical activity, and principles guiding a sound, physically active lifestyle.",
